<div id="review_2075482923" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2075482923" />
    <a title="Pramodya" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/48924120-pramodya"><img alt="Pramodya" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1498984160p2/48924120.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2075482923?book_show_action=true">Apr 17, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pramodya" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pramodya" href="/user/show/48924120-pramodya">Pramodya</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2075482923" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1260373008636784404">This was such an excellent read! I absolutely could not have picked a better book to get over my reading slump. <br/><br/>This is a brilliantly executed day-to-day or sometimes a minute-to-minute account of the Bataan death march, the imprisonment in the Cabanatuan POW camp and the subsequent, thrilling account of the rescue mission undertaken to free these POWs.<br/><br/>This was an excellent narrative of the personal experiences of the POWs and the soldiers involved in the rescue mission. The story flowed so well</span>
  <span id="freeText1260373008636784404" style="display:none">This was such an excellent read! I absolutely could not have picked a better book to get over my reading slump. <br /><br />This is a brilliantly executed day-to-day or sometimes a minute-to-minute account of the Bataan death march, the imprisonment in the Cabanatuan POW camp and the subsequent, thrilling account of the rescue mission undertaken to free these POWs.<br /><br />This was an excellent narrative of the personal experiences of the POWs and the soldiers involved in the rescue mission. The story flowed so well and was certainly bolstered by the brilliant writing by the author. <br /><br />I truly did not know much about the Bataan death march or about the POW camps operated under the Japanese. This book was a really good insight into it. There were so many moments I was sick to my stomach and moments where I struggled with my emotions while reading it. At times, I almost felt like I was there experiencing it with them.<br /><br />Also, I truly admire the unbelievable bravery and loyalty of the local Filipino civilians who were so instrumental in the liberation of these POWs. I hope history will not forget the enormous part they played in this. <br /><br />If you're wondering whether to read this, YES you should! It's an excellent book that will definitely end up in your top read lists (non-fiction history).</span>
  <a data-text-id="1260373008636784404" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


