<div id="review_4004406" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/4004406" />
    <a title="Kay" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/241691-kay"><img alt="Kay" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1638038141p2/241691.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/4004406?book_show_action=true">Aug 02, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kay" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kay" href="/user/show/241691-kay">Kay</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/241691-kay?shelf=harrowing-tales">harrowing-tales</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/241691-kay?shelf=re-reading">re-reading</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/241691-kay?shelf=world_war_ii">world_war_ii</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/241691-kay?shelf=nonfiction">nonfiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/241691-kay?shelf=available-mcpl">available-mcpl</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/241691-kay?shelf=american-histry">american-histry</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4004406" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12766924403030873896">Seventeen years ago, I listened to an audio version of this book and was captivated. Since then, I&apos;ve read three other books by Hampton Sides, all of them magnificent. Most recently, I read <i>On Desperate Ground</i>, a tale of heroism during the Korean War, and I made a mental note to go back and read <i>Ghost Soldiers</i> as my recollection of it was fuzzy, but the themes and development seemed similar. <br/><br/>In both books, he focuses on both tactical leaders and ordinary soldiers (and in neither book does he hav</span>
  <span id="freeText12766924403030873896" style="display:none">Seventeen years ago, I listened to an audio version of this book and was captivated. Since then, I've read three other books by Hampton Sides, all of them magnificent. Most recently, I read <i>On Desperate Ground</i>, a tale of heroism during the Korean War, and I made a mental note to go back and read <i>Ghost Soldiers</i> as my recollection of it was fuzzy, but the themes and development seemed similar. <br /><br />In both books, he focuses on both tactical leaders and ordinary soldiers (and in neither book does he have much good to say about General MacArthur). His ability to clarify complex military situations is a particular boon to non-military readers, and although events are portrayed realistically and at times terrifyingly, throughout are recurring motifs of human decency, fortitude, and dedication.<br /><br />I've sung Sides' praises <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1073593623?book_show_action=false&amp;from_review_page=1" rel="nofollow noopener"> elsewhere</a>, but was struck, once again, at how brilliantly he sets up and paces his books. <br /><br />Really, I have not much more to add other than to note that when I'm casting about for what to read next, increasingly I find it rewarding simply to go back and reread favorite books.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12766924403030873896" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


